<p>Resource Pooling is a fundamental cloud characteristic where computing resources are pooled to serve multiple consumers in a <span class="kh">multi-tenant model</span>, with resources <span class="kh">dynamically assigned</span> and reassigned based on consumer demand. Customers generally have no control or knowledge of the exact physical location of resources (<span class="kh">location independence</span>).</p>
