<div class="understand"><div class="ul">What it actually means</div><p>Cloud security protects data, applications, and infrastructure stored in the cloud. The challenge: in the cloud, your sensitive data is stored on someone else's servers somewhere you can't physically see or control. Security threats include hackers stealing data, someone hijacking your cloud account, or your data being accidentally exposed to other tenants.</p></div>
<div class="sec">🔑 Keywords to Memorise</div>
<div class="keywords"><div class="kl">These words MUST appear in your answer</div>
<div class="kw-grid"><span class="kw">Data breach</span><span class="kw">Denial of Service (DoS)</span><span class="kw">Account hijacking</span><span class="kw">Insecure APIs</span><span class="kw">Identity management</span><span class="kw">Access control</span><span class="kw">Encryption</span><span class="kw">Firewall</span><span class="kw">Intrusion Detection System (IDS)</span><span class="kw">SECaaS (Security as a Service)</span></div></div>

<div class="sec">✍ 5-Mark Answer</div>
<div class="ans-card"><div class="ans-head"><span>Cloud Security — Threats and Mechanisms</span><span class="m5">5 Marks</span></div>
<div class="ans-body">
<p>Cloud security protects cloud data, applications, and infrastructure from threats and unauthorised access.</p>
<p><strong>Key Threats:</strong> <span class="kh">Data breach</span> (unauthorised access to sensitive data), <span class="kh">Account hijacking</span> (credentials stolen via phishing), <span class="kh">Insecure APIs</span> (poorly designed cloud APIs exploited), <span class="kh">Denial of Service (DoS)</span> attacks (flooding servers), Insider threats.</p>
<p><strong>Security Mechanisms:</strong> <span class="kh">Encryption</span> (data encrypted at rest and in transit), <span class="kh">Firewall</span> (filter unauthorised traffic), <span class="kh">Identity management</span> and <span class="kh">Access control</span> (only authorised users access resources), <span class="kh">Intrusion Detection System (IDS)</span> (detect attacks in real time).</p>
</div></div>

<div class="sec">✍ 10-Mark Answer</div>
<div class="ans-card"><div class="ans-head"><span>Cloud Security — Complete Threats, Mechanisms, and SECaaS</span><span class="m10">10 Marks</span></div>
<div class="ans-body">
<p>Cloud security encompasses policies, technologies, and controls that protect cloud data, applications, and infrastructure from threats.</p>
<p><strong>Major Cloud Security Threats:</strong></p>
<table>
<tr><th>Threat</th><th>Description</th></tr>
<tr><td><strong>Data Breach</strong></td><td>Unauthorised access to sensitive customer or business data stored in the cloud</td></tr>
<tr><td><strong>Account Hijacking</strong></td><td>Attacker steals cloud account credentials via phishing or malware, takes full control</td></tr>
<tr><td><strong>Insecure APIs</strong></td><td>Poorly designed or unprotected cloud service APIs exploited for unauthorised access</td></tr>
<tr><td><strong>Denial of Service (DoS)</strong></td><td>Flooding cloud services with traffic to make them unavailable to legitimate users</td></tr>
<tr><td><strong>Insider Threats</strong></td><td>Malicious or careless employees misuse their access to compromise data</td></tr>
</table>
<p><strong>Information Security Methods / Mechanisms:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Encryption:</strong> Data encrypted at rest (AES-256) and in transit (TLS/HTTPS) — even if stolen, unreadable without key</li>
<li><strong>Identity Management:</strong> Multi-factor authentication (MFA), single sign-on (SSO), strong password policies</li>
<li><strong>Access Control:</strong> Role-based access control (RBAC) — users can only access what their role permits</li>
<li><strong>Firewall and IDS:</strong> Firewall filters traffic; Intrusion Detection System monitors for attack patterns in real time</li>
<li><strong>Data Storage Security:</strong> Redundant backups across multiple geographic locations</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>SECaaS (Security as a Service):</strong> <span class="kh">SECaaS (Security as a Service)</span> delivers security services over the cloud — including identity verification, virus and malware detection, intrusion management, and encryption. Benefits: reduces cost of dedicated security infrastructure, always up-to-date threat databases, elastic — scales with your cloud usage. Examples: Cloudflare (DDoS protection), Okta (identity management).</p>
</div></div>
</div>

<!-- ═══ T14: IoT INTRODUCTION ═══ -->
<div id="t14">
<div class="topic"><div class="tnum">14</div><div><div class="ttitle">Internet of Things (IoT) — Introduction</div><div class="tsub">Definition · Characteristics · Categories · Components · M2M vs IoT</div></div><span class="badge br">ALL Papers</span></div>
