<div class="sec">✍ 5-Mark Answer</div>
<div class="ans-card"><div class="ans-head"><span>IoT — Definition and Characteristics</span><span class="m5">5 Marks</span></div>
<div class="ans-body">
<p>Internet of Things (IoT) is a massive network of physical devices embedded with <span class="kh">sensors, software, electronics, and network</span> connectivity that allows devices to exchange and collect data and perform actions without human interaction.</p>
<p><strong>5 Key Characteristics of IoT:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Dynamic and Self-Adapting:</strong> <span class="kh">Dynamic and self-adapting</span> — devices adapt based on context and changing conditions</li>
<li><strong>Self-Configuring:</strong> <span class="kh">Self-configuring</span> — large numbers of devices work together automatically</li>
<li><strong>Interoperable Communication Protocols:</strong> Support multiple <span class="kh">interoperable communication protocols</span> to communicate with other devices</li>
<li><strong>Unique Identity:</strong> Each IoT device has a <span class="kh">unique identity (IP address)</span></li>
<li><strong>Integrated into Information Network:</strong> Allows exchange of data with other devices and systems</li>
